@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title State Machine - computeinstanceagent/InstanceAgentPlugin
skinparam state {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
}
left to right direction
hide empty description
state "Observe" as observe
state "EvaluateReady" as evaluate_ready
state "Ready" as ready
state "Retryable" as retryable
state "Failed" as failed
observe : read spec, tracked status, delete intent,\nand current OCI lifecycle
state "ResolveByLookup" as resolve_by_lookup
state "RejectUnsupportedDrift" as reject_unsupported_drift
[*] --> observe : reconcile
observe --> resolve_by_lookup : tracked identity missing
resolve_by_lookup --> evaluate_ready : lookup or create reaches\nRUNNING, STOPPED,\nNOT_SUPPORTED, INVALID
resolve_by_lookup --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
observe --> evaluate_ready : OCI state in RUNNING,\nSTOPPED, NOT_SUPPORTED,\nINVALID
observe --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
evaluate_ready --> reject_unsupported_drift : force-new or conflicting\ndrift detected
reject_unsupported_drift --> ready : wait for spec or live state change
evaluate_ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
retryable --> retryable : OCI remains retryable
failed --> failed : OCI remains terminal
note right of ready
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers map provider states into the shared
controller phases with explicit finalizer and
requeue policies.
service: computeinstanceagent
slug: instanceagentplugin
kind: InstanceAgentPlugin
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required / none
requeue: terminating
provider states: create none; update none;
delete none
follow-up: create=none; update=none; delete=none
supported drift: none
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId, instanceagentId, pluginName
create-only fields: none
list lookup:
oci_compute_instance_agent_instance_agent_plugins
filters compartmentId, instanceagentId,
pluginName; Direct reads require the exact
composite identity
instanceagentId+compartmentId+pluginName.
Confirmation-only list reads reuse the same
scope and treat an exact plugin-name match as
the bound plugin; unexpected surviving matches
fail instead of guessing.
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Compute Instance Agent exposes
GetInstanceAgentPlugin and
ListInstanceAgentPlugins only in the pinned SDK,
so the published runtime is bind-existing and
observe-only.
Bind identity is explicit: reconcile requires
compartmentId, instanceagentId, and pluginName,
tracks the composite identity in status, and
uses ListInstanceAgentPlugins only to confirm
absence after a reread no longer finds the
tracked plugin.
No OCI create, update, or delete operation is
published. Plugin enable or disable remains part
of Core UpdateInstance and is out of scope for
this package.
Visible plugin states RUNNING, STOPPED,
NOT_SUPPORTED, and INVALID are all stable
observed states. Delete is Kubernetes-local
unbind only and settles through best-effort
local cleanup rather than cloud-side terminal
waiting.
end note
@enduml
